PLAYWRIGHT and producer Mandla kaNoZulu has asked people not to call him “Season 2”. KaNoZulu was the brains behind Umkhokha and viewers loved it. It ended unexpectedly and it left a lot of gaps and questions which gave the impression that it will come back with a second season. Due to its intriguing storyline, many people have been calling for another season, particularly on social media. The call for Umkhokha season two is so strong that viewers have resorted to ambushing Mandla wherever he goes. In his Facebook post, he revealed that he can’t go anywhere without people shouting “Season 2”. ALSO READ : KULLERBOX AND MZUKULU CLASH OVER PHRASE! “I’ve just learned with shock that I’m now called ‘Season 2’. Even people who see me at the mall they shout ‘season 2’ we appreciate the love but my name is KaNoZulu,” he wrote. But his fans, friends and colleagues teased him some more. Pamela Nonhlanhla insisted and wrote: “Your new name is season 2. We’re asking for it please.” His friend Lindz Mhlongo said: “From now on, I’m going to start calling you season 2.” Tabsie Billy-Mata wrote: “I was starting to really enjoy Umkhokha but what did you do. Please bring back season 2.” Mpumza Matomela-Zuma posted: “Another thing that’s going to kill us is waiting for Season 2.” 